name: Black-billed Barbet
rangeDescription: Eastern sudan to western ethiopia, northeastern democratic republic of the congo, uganda, western kenya, and northern tanzania
description: A medium-sized black barbet with a mostly red head. With a good look, pale edges to the wing feathers are visible.

name: Blue-fronted Flycatcher
rangeDescription: Montane forest of central and southeastern sulawesi
description: Male shows an entirely blue hood, an olive back, and rufous underparts, including the belly. Female lacks the blue hood.

name: Rotuma Myzomela
description: A striking myzomela with beautifully contrasting plumage. Has a red chest and flanks and a bright crimson back and rump.

name: Yellow-throated Leafbird
rangeDescription: Southwestern philippines (balabac, busuanga, palawan, and calamian)
description: A medium-sized bird of lowland forest canopy and edge on Palawan and neighboring islands. Joins mixed-species flocks, often with bulbuls, foraging for fruits and seeds.

name: Burmese Myna
description: Medium-sized starling of forest edge, agricultural fields, and open scrubby or grassy areas. Thin, black bandit’s mask, medium-gray back, grayish-pink chest, dark iris and bicolored orange-and-black bill.

name: Biak White-eye
rangeDescription: Mountains of supiori and biak (cenderawasih bay, off northwestern new guinea)
description: A small bird of forest on Biak Island where it is the only white-eye. Olive-green head and back, yellow under the base of the tail, dark gray face, pale gray underparts with whitish throat and belly.

name: Piping Crow
rangeDescription: Central and southern sulawesi, muna, and buton islands
description: A distinctive black-and-white crow that occurs within the canopy of hill and mountain forest on Sulawesi and satellite islands. White parts of adults are duller on juveniles.

name: White-tailed Swallow
rangeDescription: Arid highlands of southern ethiopia (sidamo province)
description: A small swallow with white underparts and dark blue upperparts. The tail shows an unusual pattern: a dark rim around large white panels both above and below.

name: Tacarcuna Wood-Quail
rangeDescription: Far eastern panama and adjacent northwestern colombia (chocó)
description: This rare chickenlike bird has an exceptionally small range on the border between Panama and Colombia. Found on the ground in mature forest from around 1,000–1,400 m.

name: Yellow-bibbed Lory
description: A thick-set, short-tailed parrot with green wings, a red body, a black cap, purple thighs, and a yellow bib just underneath a black streak on the side of the neck that extends up toward the cap. Resident in primary forest, but tolerant of modified habitats.
imageCreditName: Lars Petersson | My World of Bird Photography

name: Heard Island Shag
description: A large pied shag with a very white head, neck, and shoulders, a bright blue eye-ring, and a large patch of yellow warty skin in front of the eyes. Breeding adult has a wispy crest.

name: Thrush Nightingale
rangeDescription: Northern eurasia; winters to eastern and southern africa
description: Very similar to Common Nightingale, but more dusky brown (not reddish-brown), with a duller and darker rufous tail and a mottled brown (not plain and sandy) breast. Their songs can be confusingly similar, but Thrush Nightingale is more monotonous, less varied, and slower, resembling that of Song Thrush.

name: Cuban Emerald
rangeDescription: Cuba including isla de la juventud (isle of pines; south of western cuba), grand bahama, great abaco, and andros
description: A pugnacious hummingbird that feeds on flowers and insects and is sometimes found flycatching. Inhabits a broad range of habitats.

name: Western Dwarf Hornbill
rangeDescription: Sierra leone to northern democratic republic of the congo (west of the congo river)
description: A small, dark forest hornbill found predominantly in primary forest subcanopy, where it prefers areas with abundant vines. This species is unique in its overall dark coloration and its broad white eyebrow that extends to the back of the head.
